===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|band|lang=enm}} (also {{term|bond|lang=enm}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|beand|lang=ang}}, {{term|bænd|lang=ang}}, {{term|bend||bond, chain, fetter, band, ribbon, ornament, chaplet, crown|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*bandą}}, {{term/t|gem-pro|*bandiz||band, fetter}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*bʰendʰ-||to tie, bind}}. {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|band|lang=enm}} reinforced by {{etyl|fro|-}} {{term|bande|lang=fro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|band|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Band|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|bånd|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|band|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|bandur||band|lang=is}}. Related to {{l/en|bond}}, {{l/en|bind}}, {{l/en|bend}}.

