# A strip along the spine of a book where the pages are attached.
# A [[belt]] or [[strap]] that is part of a [[machine]].
# {{cx|architecture|lang=en}} A continuous tablet, stripe, or series of ornaments, as of carved foliage, of colour, or of brickwork.
# {{cx|architecture|lang=en}} In Gothic architecture, the moulding, or suite of mouldings, which encircles the pillars and small shafts.
# That which serves as the means of union or connection between persons; a [[tie]].
#* Shakespeare
#*: to join in Hymen's '''bands'''
# A [[linen]] [[collar]] or [[ruff]] worn in the 16th and 17th centuries.
# {{cx|in the plural|lang=en}} Two strips of linen hanging from the neck in front as part of a clerical, legal, or academic dress.
# {{context|physics|lang=en}} A part of the [[radio]] [[spectrum]].
